Hmm?

02:15.761 --> 02:19.424
The debris and the eyewitness
accounts say it looks like a bomb.

02:19.640 --> 02:21.631
[CELL PHONE BUZZING]

02:22.559 --> 02:23.594
It's my dad.

02:23.810 --> 02:26.347
NEWS ANCHOR:
Reports are claiming
that this could be the result--

02:26.521 --> 02:29.137
Hey. Is everything okay?

02:29.358 --> 02:32.145
I can't call my daughter
unless there's something wrong?

02:32.361 --> 02:35.853
How are you feeling?
Oh, you know me. Picture of health.

02:36.531 --> 02:38.192
Something's wrong.

02:38.408 --> 02:40.364
This 12-year-old
who claims to be an oncologist

02:40.577 --> 02:42.408
wants to run another series of tests.

02:42.621 --> 02:45.738
You're in the hospital? I'm coming.
No, you're not. I'm ﬁne.

02:45.957 --> 02:48.869
Listen, butterball, it's under control.

02:49.086 --> 02:53.625
I've got teams of medical people here.
Their teams have teams. I'm fine.

02:53.840 --> 02:57.458
When are these tests happening?
As soon as the doc finishes her martini.

02:57.678 --> 03:00.340
No jokes. If this is serious,
I wanna be there.

03:01.014 --> 03:03.050
It's not.
Don 't say that because

03:03.266 --> 03:06.053
you don't wanna bother me.
You're allowed to bother me.

03:06.728 --> 03:09.105
It's just a test, Lizzy.

03:09.856 --> 03:13.223
Okay. Leave your phone on
and call me as soon as it's done, okay?

03:13.443 --> 03:14.728
All right.

03:15.320 --> 03:18.562
Dad, I love you.
[love you too.

03:19.825 --> 03:23.784
Pretending doesn't make it any better.
She deserves to know the truth.

03:23.995 --> 03:25.326
[m1

03:25.497 --> 03:28.034
Shut up and hand me
that Snickers bar, would you?

03:28.250 --> 03:31.367
Absolutely not. I'm not giving you
access to the FBI's ViCAP system.

03:31.586 --> 03:33.451
Then you have to find
another criminal

03:33.672 --> 03:36.379
to talk to Elizabeth Keen
and make fun of Agent Ressler.

03:36.591 --> 03:40.254
We have an agreement.
Yes, for me to bring cases to you.

03:40.470 --> 03:43.758
It doesn't work the other way around.
I'm not your consultant.

03:43.974 --> 03:47.762
l have no interest in cases
that l have no interest in.

03:47.978 --> 03:50.845
Personally, I think my proposal
was incredibly fair.

03:51.440 --> 03:53.806
You have got to give to get, Harold.

03:54.025 --> 03:56.641
You're asking me to go beyond
the terms of our agreement.

03:56.862 --> 03:58.853
If you want me to help you, lwill.

03:59.072 --> 04:01.688
But I need something extra
to sweeten the deal.

04:01.908 --> 04:04.695
Rest assured,
granting me access to ViCAP

04:04.911 --> 04:07.072
will benefit you just as much
as it does me.

04:07.289 --> 04:09.530
Does this mean you know
who took down that plane?

04:09.750 --> 04:12.867
You're speaking as if an individual
is responsible for this.

04:13.086 --> 04:17.125
It's far bigger than you might think.
It's a movement.

04:19.968 --> 04:22.050
Do we have a deal?

04:22.262 --> 04:24.548
[m1

04:24.723 --> 04:27.886
LIZ:
Reddington believes General Ludd
is behind the attack.

04:28.101 --> 04:32.185
They take their name from
the leader of a 19th century group
called the Luddites,

04:32.397 --> 04:36.140
a militant wing of a popular struggle
against early industrial capitalism.

04:36.359 --> 04:39.192
1997, Davos, Switzerland.

04:39.404 --> 04:42.862
Ludd took credit for a car bomb that hit
the Economic International Summit.

04:43.074 --> 04:46.612
Nine people were killed, including
two European finance ministers.

04:46.828 --> 04:49.490
2005, Ludd released the source code

04:49.706 --> 04:51.992
protecting data
for international stockholders.

04:52.209 --> 04:54.951
Caused a glitch that cost the market
a few hundred million.

04:55.170 --> 04:57.832
See, that I can appreciate.
Trim the fat off the fat cats.

04:58.048 --> 04:59.913
This group is incredibly well-educated.

05:00.133 --> 05:02.294
They're as disciplined
as any terrorist cell.

05:02.469 --> 05:04.130
Identifying members
has been impossible.

05:04.346 --> 05:06.007
Reddington can ID one of these guys?

05:06.223 --> 05:09.260
Better. Says he can identify the group's
founder, Nathaniel Wolff.

05:09.476 --> 05:12.684
Says he's the man
ultimately responsible
for taking down that plane.

05:12.896 --> 05:15.854
This is the only known image of him
that we have.

05:16.441 --> 05:17.851
Get out there. Find him.

05:18.068 --> 05:22.061
I'll let the locals know you're coming.
Nobody sleeps until we have him.

05:24.950 --> 05:27.191
AGENT:
It was definitely a bomb,
not mechanical.

05:27.410 --> 05:29.401
At the moment, we have two suspects.

05:29.621 --> 05:32.579
The bomb was homemade, straight
from the Oklahoma City playbook.

05:33.124 --> 05:35.581
It was driven onto the tarmac
by a cargo operator

05:35.794 --> 05:37.659
and placed onto the plane.

05:37.879 --> 05:40.416
We've got bomb residue inside
to confirm that.

05:40.632 --> 05:42.372
The driver's name was Roger Gard.

05:42.592 --> 05:44.969
Haven't found him.
What about your second suspect?

05:45.178 --> 05:48.136
My guys just got word last night
a fertilizer plant was robbed.

05:48.348 --> 05:51.511
One of the part-time employees stole
chemicals from the warehouse.

05:51.726 --> 05:53.432
Have a name?
Plant manager thinks

05:53.645 --> 05:56.011
it was taken by an employee named
Arthur Denning.

05:58.149 --> 06:00.140
[m1

06:21.381 --> 06:25.249
Here it is. We've got it. Arthur Denning
started at the Greenbow Fertilizer Plant

06:25.468 --> 06:26.503
three months ago.

06:26.720 --> 06:29.006
The U.S. Attorney subpoenaed
everything they have.

06:29.180 --> 06:32.308
Personal records,
performance reviews and this.

06:32.517 --> 06:33.973
Security footage.

06:34.185 --> 06:40.021
He accessed a remote warehouse
at 2:16 am.
There he is. That's our guy.

06:40.233 --> 06:43.350
That's Arthur Denning?
I just got a company ID
on Roger Gard.

06:43.570 --> 06:46.778
Aram, can you pull up that picture?
Yeah.

06:48.783 --> 06:50.910
Okay. What the hell is going on?

06:51.119 --> 06:53.906
Arthur Denning and Roger Gard
are the same person.

06:54.122 --> 06:56.579
Can you pull up the photo of Wolff?

06:59.502 --> 07:03.336
Whoever that guy is,
he is not Nathaniel Wolff.

07:03.548 --> 07:04.833
Then who is he?

07:05.050 --> 07:07.041
[m1

07:44.589 --> 07:49.083
Who has my itinerary?
Flight 1143.

07:51.972 --> 07:55.806
I want you all to know
what an honor this has been.

07:59.813 --> 08:03.556
Hey. I know you don't wanna call me
because you don't wanna freak me out

08:03.775 --> 08:07.768
but FYI, not calling me freaks me out,
so call me.

08:07.988 --> 08:11.446
I just wanna know about the tests.
I love you.

08:11.658 --> 08:13.990
We compared the employee files
of Gard and Denning.

08:14.202 --> 08:15.908
They have one thing in common.
What?

08:16.121 --> 08:18.112
We got his home address. Let's roll.

08:21.042 --> 08:23.033
[m1

08:54.409 --> 08:56.445
LIZ:
We went looking for the real identity

08:56.661 --> 08:58.652
of the man
posing as Denning and Gard.

08:58.872 --> 09:00.453
The one thing we knew going in,

09:00.665 --> 09:04.078
was that the man we were looking
for was not Nathaniel Wolff.

09:04.294 --> 09:07.582
We were wrong. Reddington was right.
What proof do you have?

09:07.797 --> 09:12.131
The items we found are basically
a love letter from Wolff to his father.

09:12.343 --> 09:15.756
Wolff's father was a mechanic who
worked his entire life at PTB Aviation.

09:15.972 --> 09:19.635
When Wolff was 6, a corporate raider
bought the airline and sold it off.

09:19.851 --> 09:22.934
Wolff's father was a union man,
fought to keep the airline intact.

09:23.146 --> 09:26.138
He lost. Started drinking, his wife left.
Six months later,

09:26.357 --> 09:30.020
Wolff's father committed suicide.
Okay. But again, that isn't proof.

09:30.236 --> 09:33.353
No, but we've got Nathaniel Wolff's
fingerprints all over the place.

09:33.573 --> 09:36.189
Two different people,
both with the exact same print?

09:36.409 --> 09:38.570
RESSLER:
He can't change his fingerprints.

09:38.787 --> 09:41.153
He changed his face.

09:42.082 --> 09:43.993
LULI:
Malaysia is the future, Mary.

09:44.209 --> 09:47.042
A new world is waiting.
They're starting a production line--

09:47.253 --> 09:49.335
I am not moving to Malaysia.

09:49.547 --> 09:53.790
I understand but with your skills
and a market like Kuala Lumpur...

09:54.010 --> 09:55.796
I find it so reassuring.

09:56.012 --> 10:00.802
The movie stars, the pop singers,
they really are just like the rest of us.

10:01.017 --> 10:02.757
Mr. Reddington, I told you,

10:02.977 --> 10:05.889
I'm not interested
in anything outside Fairfax County.

10:06.106 --> 10:08.392
Caleb's in school. He's 9.

10:08.608 --> 10:11.725
I'm treasurer of the PTA, for God sakes.
I can'tjust leave.

10:11.945 --> 10:17.156
Mary, darling, you would thrive
in Malaysia and Caleb would love it.

10:17.367 --> 10:22.578
Those thieving little monkeys
near Batu Caves are absolute rascals.

10:22.872 --> 10:24.282
[DOOR OPENS]

10:26.876 --> 10:28.457
Molly!

10:28.670 --> 10:32.208
What are you doing here?
You're a little early. We're not ready yet.

10:32.423 --> 10:35.335
One of our most trusted couriers.
Please excuse us.

10:35.552 --> 10:37.088
[m1

10:37.262 --> 10:40.754
You have a suburban housewife
printing fake money out of her garage.

10:40.974 --> 10:43.716
Mary is an artist.
She has a tremendous gift.

10:43.935 --> 10:47.143
I've been calling your people
all morning. Luli didn't pick up.

10:47.355 --> 10:49.266
Luli didn't pick up because we're busy.

10:49.482 --> 10:51.814
You should've dug
that chip out of your damn neck.

10:52.527 --> 10:55.109
Well, you're here now,
so, what's on your mind?

10:55.321 --> 10:58.188
We searched the home address
listed for both suspects

10:58.408 --> 11:00.319
and were able to pull some prints.

11:00.535 --> 11:01.991
They belong to Nathaniel Wolff.

11:02.328 --> 11:03.443
RAUGHS]

11:03.621 --> 11:07.955
I never tire of being correct.
Someone changed his face.

11:09.961 --> 11:12.498
I understand your father is not well.

11:13.298 --> 11:16.085
Excuse me?
The cancer, it's come back?

11:16.301 --> 11:18.917
My father's fine, he's just...

11:19.804 --> 11:21.180
Who the hell told you that?

11:22.140 --> 11:25.724
You should be there. With him.

11:26.769 --> 11:28.430
I'm not doing this.

11:28.646 --> 11:30.898
Guessing what you know
or how you know it.

11:31.107 --> 11:32.142
Dr. Maltz.

11:32.358 --> 11:34.849
What?
Abraham Maltz.

11:35.069 --> 11:38.232
The best surgeon
for this sort of business.

11:42.744 --> 11:44.450
Maltz.

11:44.662 --> 11:46.653
[m1

11:51.836 --> 11:53.576
Before we do this,
let me be clear.

11:53.796 --> 11:56.173
I have business that requires further
travel today.

11:56.382 --> 11:59.124
So this needs to happen quickly,
you need to follow my lead.

11:59.344 --> 12:02.552
Dr. Maltz is not on the Blacklist,
he's an asset I need to protect.

12:02.764 --> 12:06.723
You want me to protect
some surgeon who might be linked
to a terrorist organization?

12:06.935 --> 12:08.641
Yes.

12:09.479 --> 12:10.639
Abraham.

12:10.855 --> 12:13.517
Raymond. What brings you in?
I don't know how you do it.

12:13.733 --> 12:17.225
I had that done once,
couldn't bear the tickling. How are you?

12:17.445 --> 12:20.858
We need to talk. In private.
Yeah, sure. Give us a minute, please?

12:22.158 --> 12:24.991
Ray, look at you.
You look great.

12:25.203 --> 12:27.910
I mean, the elasticity is amazing.

12:28.122 --> 12:29.157
You've been juicing?

12:29.374 --> 12:31.990
Beets, mostly.
Some celery, carrots, a lot of ginger.

12:32.210 --> 12:34.166
The kale makes me dyspeptic.

12:34.379 --> 12:37.496
And what's a beautiful young woman
like you doing with this vulture?

12:37.715 --> 12:39.546
Trust me, it's not by choice.

12:39.759 --> 12:43.547
So, Nathaniel Wolff, you gave him
a new face. I need to find him.

12:44.347 --> 12:46.053
You know I would help you if I could.

12:46.266 --> 12:48.097
I do and I thank you for that, Abraham.

12:48.309 --> 12:52.393
Normally I wouldn't impose but this is
a personal matter of some urgency.

12:52.981 --> 12:55.973
You know my business, the rules.
It's all about confidentiality.

12:56.192 --> 12:59.730
Absolutely. This conversation
should never leave this office.

12:59.946 --> 13:03.359
I just got done with six hours
of surgery and you walk in.

13:03.574 --> 13:07.487
I mean, I don't know you or why you
think you could come in here

13:07.704 --> 13:10.366
and ask questions about my clients.
Red, help me out.

13:10.581 --> 13:13.664
My name is Special Agent
Elizabeth Keen. I'm with the FBI.

13:14.210 --> 13:18.499
Mr. Reddington is working with us,
helping us to capture high-value targets

13:18.715 --> 13:22.708
and Nathaniel Wolff is one of them.
I need to find Wolff. I know you can help.

13:22.927 --> 13:25.760
Wait a minute.
You're an informant now?

13:25.972 --> 13:27.758
How dare you come--?
LIZ: Did you hear me?

13:27.974 --> 13:31.558
I need his new name. Give it to me
or I'll have the Miami Field Office

13:31.769 --> 13:34.761
tear your practice apart
faster than you can say "tummy tuck."

13:36.190 --> 13:39.899
Bradley Holland, okay?
That's the name he goes under now.

13:40.111 --> 13:41.521
Bradley Holland.

13:42.238 --> 13:44.103
Abraham.

13:44.324 --> 13:50.194
I refer important clients to you,
people who are vital to my business.

13:50.413 --> 13:53.746
People whose livelihood
depends on your confidentiality,

13:53.958 --> 13:56.950
and you roll over like a cockapoo
wanting his belly scratched?

13:57.170 --> 13:59.161
You said this guy was solid.
RAYMOND: Some woman

13:59.380 --> 14:01.336
Wait.
who claims to be an FBI agent

14:01.549 --> 14:03.631
makes a few ham-fisted threats,

14:07.055 --> 14:09.888
God forbid this ever gets back
to poor Nathaniel Wolff.

14:10.099 --> 14:13.637
I don't know what's-- Nothing.
What other secrets have you given away?

14:13.853 --> 14:17.562
Who knows about the work I had done?
Nobody, truthfully. You know me.

14:17.774 --> 14:21.437
I brought Christina to you specifically
for your discretion and expertise.

14:21.652 --> 14:23.813
I assured her you were trustworthy.

14:23.988 --> 14:26.104
I'm sorry. I was wrong.

14:26.324 --> 14:27.359
Shame on you, Abraham.

14:27.575 --> 14:29.156
I know another doctor.
No. Red.

14:29.369 --> 14:31.826
We could make this right.
You know me.

14:32.038 --> 14:34.825
I would never give out
a name of any client.

14:35.041 --> 14:36.656
[m1

14:39.629 --> 14:42.837
LIZ:
We believe Wolff is now
using the name, Bradley Holland,

14:43.049 --> 14:44.380
a pilot for Innova Air.

14:44.550 --> 14:47.166
I buy him as a cargo operator,
but a pilot?

14:47.387 --> 14:50.254
That would require licenses,
documentation, a background check.

14:50.473 --> 14:54.057
Anonymity is a cornerstone
of this group's decentralized
command structure.

14:54.268 --> 14:56.645
Wolff has given up his identity
for this cause.

14:56.854 --> 15:00.767
Wall Street destroyed the airline
that Wolff's father devoted his life to

15:00.983 --> 15:04.726
so Wolff is now using the airlines
in his efforts to destroy Wall Street.

15:04.946 --> 15:07.733
Holland swiped through security
at Reagan International.

15:07.949 --> 15:11.362
Get the TSA on the line. Tell them to pull
the feeds. Backtrack the swipe.

15:11.577 --> 15:14.410
He's gonna bring down another plane.

15:17.750 --> 15:19.741
[m1

15:30.263 --> 15:32.970
Sophie, hi.

15:33.182 --> 15:35.798
If it's okay with you,
I'm deadheading to Denver.

15:36.018 --> 15:37.974
Let me check what seats are available.

15:38.187 --> 15:41.725
I appreciate that. I'm Bradley.

16:00.209 --> 16:01.949
[WHISPERS]
There's an empty seat in first.

16:05.256 --> 16:07.292
Must be my lucky day.

16:24.150 --> 16:27.108
Yes, sir, the attack is imminent.
We need to contact Homeland,

16:27.320 --> 16:29.060
move the threat level
to Code Red.

16:29.280 --> 16:31.020
All planes need to be rerouted.

16:31.240 --> 16:33.617
Nothing should be taking Off
or landing at Reagan.

16:40.082 --> 16:41.822
MAN:
How about that?

16:44.253 --> 16:45.288
Nuts, right?

16:47.673 --> 16:50.585
They're saying a father and son
were killed on the ground.

16:50.801 --> 16:53.759
It's terrible. That group?

16:53.971 --> 16:57.714
The ones that took credit?
Oh, yeah, General something.

16:57.934 --> 16:59.390
General... General Ludd.

16:59.602 --> 17:02.184
Within an hour
of that plane dropping out of the sky,

17:02.396 --> 17:04.978
that company lost 30 percent
of its market share.

17:08.736 --> 17:11.694
Bunch of wackos, right?
Oh, you said it.

17:11.906 --> 17:16.070
Out of work, sexually frustrated,
Iiving-at—home losers, if you ask me.

17:16.619 --> 17:18.155
Mm-hm.

17:19.205 --> 17:20.661
What line of work are you in?

17:20.873 --> 17:23.865
Hedge funds. Dolus Capital.

17:24.043 --> 17:25.579
Oh, heh-heh.

17:26.170 --> 17:28.377
So this General Ludd group,
you're, like,

17:28.589 --> 17:30.295
the poster child
for everything they hate.

17:30.466 --> 17:33.333
Ha-ha-ha.
How does that feel? You worried?

17:33.553 --> 17:37.421
Not in the Gold Club, I'm not.
Ha-ha. Know what I'm saying?

17:38.015 --> 17:39.516
Mm-hm.

17:40.601 --> 17:42.592
[m1

17:53.322 --> 17:56.564
Sophie? Do me a favor?
Whatever you need.

17:57.326 --> 18:02.161
I left my logbook six gates away.
Would you watch my stuff?

18:02.373 --> 18:05.035
I'll put it in first class.
We're boarding any minute.

18:05.751 --> 18:07.161
You're the best.

18:10.339 --> 18:12.079
Tom.
TOM: Liz, Aunt June cal/ed.

18:12.300 --> 18:13.665
Now's not a good time.

18:13.884 --> 18:16.626
She said your dad hasn't exactly been
telling you the truth.

18:16.846 --> 18:19.007
He's a little sicker
than he's been letting on.

18:19.223 --> 18:22.010
Aunt June gets indigestion
and thinks she's having a stroke.

18:23.227 --> 18:24.967
The cancer spread to his liver.

18:26.355 --> 18:27.856
What?

18:28.608 --> 18:30.564
No, he was just going in for a few tests.

18:30.776 --> 18:33.153
Apparently it's a little more serious
than that,

18:33.362 --> 18:36.104
and Aunt June thinks that
we need to be there, like, now.

18:36.657 --> 18:38.613
I can't, I...

18:39.285 --> 18:40.775
Oh, my God, I've gotta call him.

18:40.995 --> 18:44.408
No, he's in surgery. Listen,
I’m on the next flight out of Dulles,

18:44.624 --> 18:46.489
and I got Ellie to watch Hudson...

